{"title":"BLKTEC Shows Ultralight Bar-Stem, C1D Wheels & 13g Bottle Cage","link":"https://bikerumor.com/blktec-handlebars-and-wheels-taipei-2024/","date":1712780877000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-07-1536x1152.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" alt=\"blktec L8 lightweight one-piece handlebar and stem\" /></p>\n<p>BLKTEC’s new L8 one-piece handlebar-and-stem combo is as light as 245g, which they say is likely the lightest such part on the market. They’ve also updated their gravel bike bars, have a new gravel post, lighter wheels, and more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All BLKTEC handlebars are now compatible with most stealth routing systems and headsets, letting you choose the shape and style you like without giving up your bike’s aesthetics.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-06.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-06-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"blktec L8 lightweight one-piece handlebar and stem\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-06-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-06-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-06-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-06-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-06.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-02.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-02-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"top down view of blktec L8 lightweight one-piece handlebar and stem\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-02-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-02-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-02-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-02-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-02.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The L8 has a cover to keep the stem bolts concealed…</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-05.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1013\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-05-1536x1013.jpg\" alt=\"integrated computer mount for blktec L8 lightweight one-piece handlebar and stem\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-05-1536x1013.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-05-297x196.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-05-120x79.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-05-768x506.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-L8-full-integrated-handlebar-05.jpg 1820w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>…and an available direct-mount computer mount keeps it clean and very lightweight. The bar comes in 380/400/420mm widths with 90/100/110/120/130mm length stems with -10º angle. Reach is 72mm, drop is 125mm, and they have a mild 5º flare. Claimed average weight is 320g, still not bad. MSRP is $610.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-carbon-road-and-gravel-bike-handlebars.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"972\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-carbon-road-and-gravel-bike-handlebars-1536x972.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-carbon-road-and-gravel-bike-handlebars-1536x972.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-carbon-road-and-gravel-bike-handlebars-297x188.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-carbon-road-and-gravel-bike-handlebars-120x76.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-carbon-road-and-gravel-bike-handlebars-768x486.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-carbon-road-and-gravel-bike-handlebars.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The BLKTEC gravel handlebars come in both 12/24° flare options. The R6 road riser bar has a bit of flex built in, plus 20mm rise and ergonomically shaped tops for more comfort on long rides.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The R7 is an ergo-aero bar, with softer edges and more shaping than the R1.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-13g-bottle-cage-and-gravel-seatpost.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-13g-bottle-cage-and-gravel-seatpost-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"BLKTEC 13 gram lightweight carbon bottle cage and flex gravel seatpost\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-13g-bottle-cage-and-gravel-seatpost-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-13g-bottle-cage-and-gravel-seatpost-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-13g-bottle-cage-and-gravel-seatpost-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-13g-bottle-cage-and-gravel-seatpost-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/BLKTEC-13g-bottle-cage-and-gravel-seatpost.jpg 2000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>On the left is their 13g bottle cage, called Bi, which retails for $98. On the right is the new S6 gravel seatpost with Dyneema for improved vibration damping. Available in 31.6 and 27.2 diameters.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-02.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1113\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-02-1536x1113.jpg\" alt=\"BLKTEC C1D one-piece carbon fiber road bike wheels on Inner titanium gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-02-1536x1113.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-02-297x215.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-02-120x87.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-02-768x556.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-02.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Their full-carbon one-piece C1D wheels get lighter by switching to DT Swiss 180 Ratchet EXP hub internals. They’re shown here on an Inner gravel bike, a new bike brand launching out of Australia later this year.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-01.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1234\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-01-1536x1234.jpg\" alt=\"BLKTEC C1D one-piece carbon fiber road bike wheels\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-01-1536x1234.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-01-297x239.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-01-120x96.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-01-768x617.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-01-2048x1645.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-03.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-03-1536x1152.jpg\" alt=\"BLKTEC C1D one-piece carbon fiber road bike wheels\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-03-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-03-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-03-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-03-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/tpe-24-BLKTEC-C1D-one-piece-carbon-wheels-03.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>They also reworked the layup. Combined, they’re 150g lighter at ~1350g with CeramicSpeed bearings inside. They say it’ll Be UCI legal soon, too. They’re also working on a climber version around 1200g, and a deeper 65mm aero version. The hookless rim is optimized for 25-35mm wide tires. MSRP is $4,880.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.blktec.com\" target=\"_blank\">BLKTEC.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/blktec-handlebars-and-wheels-taipei-2024/\">BLKTEC Shows Ultralight Bar-Stem, C1D Wheels &amp; 13g Bottle Cage</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"435b0d82bab0632fc066fa6a4a94653576428e159bd22514c112511bea2562c2","category":"Cycling"}